Been feeling really really good lately with my training and diet consistency. Going now on six weeks of following the plan to a T. It’s truly amazing what your body can do when you fire on all cylinders and stay consistent.

My strength has been steadily increasing and my stamina in the gym is getting better and better. I’m finding a groove where I can do a 12 to 15 rep range for much heavier weight than I’ve ever been able to do while still recovering very well. 

Currently 24 weeks out, really excited to start this push for the next 10 to 12 weeks and beyond excited to start prep for Jr USAs! 🙏🏻 let’s keep it rolling!

Leg day- the greatest love / hate story ever told ❤️💔

I remember when I first got into lifting I HATED leg day 😅 I would always skip it when I didn’t feel like doing it and I remember someone looking at me and saying “fake it until you make it, walk into the gym and tell yourself leg day is your favorite day and you’re stoked about it..” seems far fetched but it worked lol. 

I forced myself to train legs twice a week, I forced myself to love the training and now when leg day rolls around I couldn’t be more stoked about it! Something about those days that leave you absolutely exhausted.. you just feel as if you have truly given the workout your all.. And I love that feeling!

* 3. Chest support db rows- 3 set of 15,12,10

* 4. Seated wide bar cable rows- 15,12,10,drop set

* 6. Straight bar curls / ez bar reverse grip curls- 3 sets superset back and forth of 10-12 reps

Stop going through the motions! 

One thing that has really helped me level up my physique the last couple years is training with intent and much more intensity!

Morning thoughts: don’t chase the money… hear me out lol. 

I remember when I first started doing this and started making a little money I was so obsessed with making more and more and more. What I found was the more I focused on money, the more stressful life was, the less I focused on my actual craft (bodybuilding / coaching). 

Focus on your craft, get into the profession you love and work to be the absolute best you can be at it. The money will follow. Once I stopped focusing on money and started focus on working my a$$ off everyday, week, month and year, that’s when life took its turn and everything started lining up. 

The LOVE of money is the route of all evil. Ain’t nothing wrong with wanting it, getting it, working for it BUT I will guarantee you if you put your heart, blood, sweat and tears into your craft and chase greatness, the money will follow. 

Have a relentless pursuit for greatness. Never accept average.

Mindset is everything and my mindset is dangerous right now. I know what I can do if I work hard enough and best believe imma do it. 

Because i want that feeling.. that moment..seconds before they call your name.. the second they hand you the trophy.. seconds before doing your posing routine.. hugs from friends and family, the silent moments with yourself before you hit the stage.. and then the confidence knowing you’re about to absolutely CRUSH IT… I love it, I want it. I’ll get it. It’s coming. 

2023 was fun.. but now things are different, mindsets different, goals are different, physique is different and these little incremental changes I’ve made are nothing compared to what’s to come. Let’s work. 😈

“If you spend your whole life waiting for the storm, you’ll never get to enjoy the sunshine.”

The journey from where I was to where I am now has been a very interesting one. Somtimes we downplay our issues and problems because they don’t seem so bad in the whole scope of this world. We choose to say things like oh well, they have it worse than me, or I shouldn’t complain, it’s not that bad. But one problem is no bigger than another, everyone is dealing with something, going through something, battling something. So understand that your problem, your battle, your situation, your feelings matter. And that you can and will get through it, there is sunshine at the end of it all. Don’t downplay what you’re going through for the benefit of others, walk right through it! Battle it! Defeat it!!
